intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: well go for Ankara then we need to head towards germany to confront France/Eng.... sooner Turkey dies the sooner you can get some fleets out to help me against France too!!
1 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: right... so how are we going to split up Turkey? also need to get your fleet into Aegan at some point to help push back France.
2 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: Up North I reckon you should think about abandon Sweden to price open St Petes this turn.... then you can flood armies into Finland and consider building Northern Fleets again. This might be your last chance to open up that passage before England re-inforce from German gains. You could even have Germany take Sweden from you by retreating from Denmark. And he uses his Baltic fleet to defend Kiel.
3 RUSSIA -> AUSTRIA: Yes, I am talking with Germany about a Northern plan very similar to that. Let's hope England doesn't think of it, too! But I agree, the time to reclaim St. Pete is now or never. ~N~ ~N~ As for the south... I think the best split would be you taking Con and me taking Smy. We can figure out how to facilitate the move of my fleet into the Aegean after we remove the blockade of Turkish fleet by taking all his Scs. Right now, though, I can support you into Con, and hopefully we will be able to move Ank -> Smy in the fall. We will see how Turkey disbands... ~N~ ~N~ What about the east? Will you be concentrating on Italy for a while?
4 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: Well am concentrating on keeping France out of Italy as a priority. But once Turkey is done, might be able to think about grabbing Italy for myself. If we can hold France this turn, then I think there could be room to smash through him into the West Med. He's very light on fleets and if we can breakthru to Tyrrh then the whole game opens up. ~N~ ~N~ Your support to Const. would be appreciated - though plan b might to that you take all of Turkey and I take Rumania instead. Easier for us both to defend our gains then. Just a thought.
5 RUSSIA -> AUSTRIA: Yes, I like the idea of you taking Rum while I take Con and Smy. That will give an easier route for me to exit my fleet, and it does seem that Con for Rum is a natural exchange. Do you prefer this plan?

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> FRANCE: Hmm. What is with the move to Marseilles. That is hardly comforting
1 FRANCE -> ITALY: Sorry to surprise you. I did not know if I could trust Germany so I wanted to cover Mar, which I would never be able to reclaim from him. Luckily, he did not attack me. But I do think we should look toward the future. I see Russia getting a lot of builds from A/H and Turkey. Could you tell me a little bit about your plan with Russia?
2 FRANCE -> ITALY: To be perfectly clear I would highly prefer to work with you than against you. I see a creeping Russian empire, but you and I have kept a peaceful border throughout the game and good relations. I think we should leverage that into some cooperation in containing what I suspect is your primary threat. Is there anything that I can do to help you with Russia?
3 ITALY -> FRANCE: That makes very good sense to me. The plan had roughly been to dismantle Turkey with me taking a good portion of the supply centers in exchange for Romania and Budapest. Question is whether Russia is planning to stab me or not.
4 ITALY -> FRANCE: Do you have any insight into Germany's thinking about Russia? He hasn't responded to me.
5 FRANCE -> ITALY: I think Germany is on the fence. He's got two Russian fleets up top and that Finland army--GERMANY will need a fleet build to get a better position on Russia. I think Germany will work with us against the Russian. And Turkey? He has no friends otherwise--he'd certainly help you with Russia if you helped him get a build. I will do what I can from here and I wish you luck.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> GERMANY: Builds are done, you've been back in 3 hrs.

Come on - look at France - you have a superb chance to take down France here - Munich to Bur, Bel to Pic, and you are guaranteed Paris in the Autumn, possibly Brest and Paris too.
1 GERMANY -> ITALY: I know this. But I am already at war with ENG and RUS, potentially with you and AUS also, so attacking FRA makes not much sense to me.

I need one sure ally in the South East. If you can come up with an overall plan that you can stick to and makes you comfortable chances are I'll accept it. But it needs to include you hitting AUS. That's the only way I will consider going against FRA. Otherwise I have no incentive to stop FRA attacking you also - actually it even makes sense for me to help him attack you - then he's not going to think about turning on me.

What would you suggest as an approach for the east part of the map?
2 ITALY -> GERMANY: If you could mop up the remains of Russia and England, letting me and Austria take out Turkey for 1 year without attacking France, that would give me enough breathing space to then turn on Austria.

As you are well aware, I simply can't attack Austria now whilst Turkey is still alive - Russia doesn't matter so much, but it could be enough of a distraction for a year to allow me to finish off Turkey with Austria's help.

You and France could continue to attack England, A/I attack R/T. Once E/R/T are finished off, it comes down to 4. I will attack Austria straight away, particularly given that I can line myself up in advance - I should only need a few units of yours - maybe 2-3 to tie up enough of Austria's units to ensure his defeat whilst allowing you to tackle France.

From there, I can return and assist you by putting pressure on France in the south.
3 GERMANY -> ITALY: Sorry man, I think I will remain in the area for the time-being. I don't have a clear plan, but I am not inclined to move back. I believe this pressure will have some impact.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> TURKEY: So I see you've been persuaded by Austria to join him. I don't blame you; you were trapped in that corner with nowhere to go, however I wonder where he could be offering you Scs in return for your help. He is so much larger he could basically take what he wants from me.

In addition, he's stabbed you before, and is highly likely to do so again. Be under no illusion that if and when my threat is neutralised he will turn right around and gobble you up. In your position as you were last turn you were basically secure; he couldn't defeat you without another fleet bordering Smyr, which I would have easily stopped. Now you're much more vulnerable.

I'd love it if you could reconsider your decision and join our side. England, France and I are already working together as I'm sure you've deduced, and we're set to win the fight quite easily at the moment. Our alliance was formed to stop the Austria-germany alliance, and as such our current agreement is a three way draw. We would be very willing to open that to a four way on the same understanding. As for your possible SC gains, Bulgaria, Greece, Rumania and Sevastopol would be obvious locations for Turkish occupation. Let me know your thoughts.
1 TURKEY -> ITALY: I was hoping to speak to you actually. Austria has betrayed me twice, and now it is my turn to betray them. I have given the illusion that we are in am alliance, but I only said that so.he would free up units from around me. Now I am much more set up to attack him if I so wish.

Make no mistake, I am fully against him. Tell me what you need me to do and I would love to end in a draw with the three of you.
2 ITALY -> TURKEY: Excellent. Well obviously at the moment I need you to prove your intentions so I'll leave that to you, but might I suggest slipping Aeg into Bul and Eastern to Aeg? It guarantees you a build and will split Austria's attention nicely.
3 TURKEY -> ITALY: That was my original plan.

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: I have worked things out with France to a reasonable degree so I'm hopeful he will not be helping England out in the near term. now if I do decide to keep Burgundy or take Pic, then yes, he'll probably work against me in the fall.

For the time being, my #1 fear is Baltic Sea. that is far too dangerous a spot for me to allow England into and it would truly cost me if he managed to slip there then to berlin or kiel. I have to cover it.

Also - it looks like you are making some headway in the south no? most likely you'll get black sea this spring as turkey covers ankara and smy covers con dont you think? My understanding regarding Sweden was that you had offered it to me this year. am I recollecting correctly?

Of course, if I can convoy across successfully and get edi, then that is a moot point, I will have the build I need to face off against F (and I was hoping for italian help though now that he and austria are fighting, i'm not so sure I'll get it). But if I can't get Edi this year, if I'm blocked etc, i was hoping to pick up a build from sweden.

one idea that might help us both is if you move Norway to Norwegian and Stp to Norway, that way we will have two on edi and 3 on swe (or 2 if he bounces you) and we can ensure two builds between us, in which case we can split them.

what do you think of that idea? to move nwy to nwg?
1 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: Yeah, I like that idea. I am just a bit apprehensive of England moving to Finland. In which case, I'd have to cover St P with A NOR and thus be unable to help you into Sweden.

I am very happy helping you get Sweden if I see that you are committed to moving against France. Otherwise, I am apprehensive about giving you another build. I am sure you understand. So if you make an attempt to hold Burgundy (or take Picardy, I think that would be easier), I will be happy to support you into Sweden. If not, I'll have to wait and see how the situation looks in the fall.

Also, I don't think Austria and Italy are fighting. Italy asked Austria to waive his build and it looks like Austria acquiesced.

I also expect that Black Sea and Smyrna will bounce in Ankara. Turkey has might quite clear that he'll cede his centers to Austria instead of Italy and I.
2 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: really? why would turkey do that? he attacked you not the other way around - and austria stabbed him after he gave austria help. does not make too much sense to me. I'll talk to turkey and see if he can be convinced to see the danger of austria. thanks for point out the waived build, I did think something was amiss last turn but did not pay enough attention to note it. you are right. what happened with the move to gre and gre to ion then? do you know?

as for sweden, I would want my build exactly to be able to go after france. I will continue to press against france, you'll see that. so hopefully this should not be an issue.

are you going to take nwg then? that will be very important in order to figure out edi/swe - like I said, I think we can figure it out in a way that we each get one build and we would not have to pick one over the other.
3 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: Yes, I am going to take Norwegian.

Austria promised Italy Greece, and Austria said that he'd move to Aegean with Eastern Med's support. I think Austria's move to Ion was just a misorder but I'm not entirely sure.

As for Turkey, I don't know why he's giving Austria his centers, but he's publicly announced it.
4 GERMANY -> RUSSIA: publicly? like to you guys in the south?

ahhh... the italy/austria situation now makes more sense. so that's why he did not build. so does this mean they are going to be allied now? where does that leave you with austria you think?

i was hoping italy would get a build and help with france, I can still hope for a move to pie, but i'm not entirely sure if it will materialize.

i think if we each get a build this season, that would make things much easier for us next year. I just hope that France does not retreat from England, that would be the worst outcome of my move to bur. =(
5 RUSSIA -> GERMANY: I dont know, its tough to read Austria. He is saying all the right things. I think you have a shot convincing Italy to go to Piedmont; the deferred build should mean he's pretty trusting of Austria.

And yes, Turkey sent all three of us identical messages saying that unless we stopped attacking him, he'd give Austria all of his centers. I assumed it was just a desperate gambit but so far it appears to have been a credible threat.

Was the Burgundy move prearranged? France says it was; but I don't understand why he would tell me that (regardless of whether he's lying or not)

Thanks for still keeping an eye on this game.

2 TURKEY -> GERMANY: Something to think about: if Russia does move to Prussia-silesia-bohemia, his border with me will be completely emptied while I'll still have armies stacked up along it. Then I really could pull off that crippling blow I talked about earlier. If you want your Russia problem to become a temporary minor nuisance, this is a good way to do it!

0 ENGLAND -> TURKEY: Oy. He's reneging on deals now, and there's little I can do about it.

If you were me, what would you do? Trying to figure out what isn't just a fancy way of getting myself killed.
1 TURKEY -> ENGLAND: well he is going to steam roll italy in the south but he cant afford to move MAO to irish yet in case italy tries for it. i would convoy edi to norway with stp support and move liver to wales. have skag support den in case germany goes for it. he will then likely be in the channel and hopefully only the channel. have wales cover london and take sweden. if he has EC and irish then have wales cover liver and convoy norway back to london, stp to norway and denmark support skag to sweden.

if he moves to both then it will be riskier but you should be able to defend and get a build which will definitely be fleet liver if you can. remember if youre not his ally then i think nobody is and hes not strong enough to solo yet. use italy and russia for help, maybe even austria too
2 ENGLAND -> TURKEY: Sound advice all around. Thanks.

I don't think he's moving directly against me yet (knock on wood), but it's good to be prepared.

0 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Good morning Austria. Things are looking well for us, indeed.
Next turn we'll get you into west med, and I see Sev has fallen already. I'll move back to Ank to keep it safe...
Heard anything from England? I've been keeping my distance so far just so as not to tip off France, but now I'm going to make an approach. Also, has Germany expressed any kind of plan to you? I'm sure he has everything under control- I guess- but I'd help him out more if I knew what he was doing in advance.
1 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Yeah, that went well, the Frenchman even thinks I'm attacking you since I'm in Tunis!

Haven't heard much from England lately, no, but as you say, it is time to approach him. Germany hasn't said too much either, it's been pretty quiet except for us. Tunis will attack West Med, you should probably support me in to make sure I get out, but Tyrr could do it while North Africa takes a shot at MAO and Tus hits Lyo, unless you want Tyrr to make sure you get into Lyo, then North Africa could support me into West Med, however you want to work it.

Gol is the sure thing, so I'm going to aim for that.
Do you wan to bounce in Ank to protect Con, too?
3 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: However you want to do it, but Tunis is attacking West Med.

4 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Nah, no need, just wondered.
Ankara's probably going to want to head towards the front soon, probably. I mean, I suppose I could always use it as a garrison force, but we may want it if we choose to eat Germany.
He'll sit in Ank for now but let me know if and when you want him to start marching west.
5 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: I've got plenty of armies for Germany, I think he can just chill in Turkey. He could even sit in Con (next year) while I leave an army in Bul, until you start killing off France and we shift Turkey into my possession, but I think we're good for this season.

We have some time, but I think the following moves make sense and welcome any feedback:

Italy: PIE > TYR; TUS > VEN; GOL > TYR; WES > TUN
France: NAF > WES; BUR > MUN; MAR > BUR; GAS > PAR; IRI > MAO
England: ENG > BEL; LIV > WAL; NTH S ENG > BEL; NOR H; STP H

3 ENGLAND -> ITALY: Here is my answer and France agreed with slight changes...

So I have checked Italy and you have bought us both. About moves, I have second thoughts. Escape route from BEL is PIC, so you need to be able to defend Brest. Further on we will not be able to keep BEL (possible situation is G army in PIC, RUH, fleet in HOL and DEN could cut NTH).

My idea (Italy's moves stay the same):
England: NTH>SKA, EC>NTH, LIV>WAL, NOR S NTH>SKA (attacking SWE or DEN,), STP S MOS
France: IRI>EC (to attack BEL), NAF>MAO (defending BRE), GAS>PAR, BUR>MUN, MAR>BUR
4 ITALY -> ENGLAND: One reason France proposed different moves to those was to get more fleets in the Mediterranean, so I'm cautious about keeping both his fleets up north. You could cover Brest using France's Irish Sea fleet (once it's moved to EC), meaning the North Africa fleet could stay in the Med?

Regarding the other changes I'll leave that to you two as it concerns the northern theatre. However I do agree that Bel will be harder to defend in the short term until France's army moves through Paris to Pic. I like the idea of moving to Ska to worry Swe, but you simply must make sure that the North Sea is yours, otherwise we're in big trouble.

intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: So what is our plan this turn? Should we cycle towards Turkey now? I'm going to check with the Russian. Thoughts?
1 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Hmm that is what I am planning. I ams till wary of France, but I think I've been idle for too long. What do you think?
2 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: France just told me he and England are working together on Germany. We need to move quickly now to get anywhere because Germany won't last long if they are on board together.
3 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: You know what, I think France is probably going to go MAO-WMED and MAR-GOL then, now that I think about it. If he and England are working together, then what else does he do with those two fleets? I think you probably want to bounce one of the two moves with Tyrsea. Russia is a bit too big for me and I think Turkey and I could conceivably concentrate on knocking him down a peg or two.

If we attack Turkey now while France is now heading towards you, that may be a bad plan, right? Otherwise, you, me and Turkey all die a bloody death, I think. What are your thoughts?
4 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Hmm I'm not sure what France is doing exactly. I don't think they'll necessarily move on me now. I doubt they'll want to be taking on Germany, Russia and I. They will in the near future though. I'm not sure if I want to wait for that to happen, so I might as well do it preemptively. Hmm. Have you been talking to Turkey? Are they willing to do that? Do you know what their plan in Aegean is?
5 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: I sent Turkey a message with some suggestions and am waiting to hear back. The plans include Aegean, so once I hear back, I will let you know ASAP so we can coordinate everything. At this stage of negotiations with him, I have no indication Aegean would go towards Ionian if you are worried about that.

How would you feel about supporting Burgundy to Belgium? I would absolutely support you to Holland in return.

If you're not up for that, it's fine and I will still support you to Belgium. I just thought it was worth talking about.
4 GERMANY -> FRANCE: OK I can support you to Bel then.
5 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Ok thanks.

intent_dialogue:
0 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Looking eastward, it looks like Russia and Turkey played a phoney war just long enough to make it difficult to get everyone to oppose their juggernaut. It was well done actually & might give them the game.
1 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Well, I can't trust you enough to leave ruhr as a dmz. Since you clearly will take what you can when you have sufficient force. Too bad. Why not have burgandy as a dmz? If you want to screw me over bel, you can, but don't pretend it was anything having to do with an alliance anyting else. I can't trust you. that's too bad. You let England off the hook and you cost yourself an ally. When you got bel was still up inthe air. [1179252] to build another fleet. Such is dip lirfe. Good luck to you though.
2 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I'm sorry that you feel that way. No it certainly wasn't according to any alliance as we hadn't been behaving like allies until that point. I'm very trusting of my allies and generally leave my borders open to them. What I was seeing from you though set my radar off. Again it was a move because of maybe.

Still though, you admit that your intention was to build another fleet. That is pretty much an admission that you intended to keep Belgium for long enough to keep youself from losing that additional fleet. As it stand though, the new fleet is blue and I'm willing to work with you on how it's to be deployed.

I'm not really bantering over the morality of the issue. If we were being truly moral the Belgians would rule Belgium and the Dutch, [1413210], Portuge', and [215948] would be autonomous too. Certainly, I was able to take Belgium and I did. A point that I was up front with you about. When the roles were reversed you did the same. Belgium originally belonged to the Belgians did it not? If anything, you've seen that I will be honest about my intentions even in a situation in which it would be easier to lie.
3 FRANCE -> GERMANY: You should really be looking at Warsaw and Moscow. I'm sure that you're as surprised as I am that at least one of those builds wasn't a fleet on the North Coast of St. Pete.

I think our problem is that our playing styles are very similar and we're both used to other people seeing that our ideas have merit and going along with them. Hence we're butting heads when we'd be better served by turning our attention elsewhere.

If you are willing to set a plan that shows equal growth for both of our nations then I'm your guy. If you insist on a junior partner, then it's going to be a frustrating game for both of us.

That being said, We are in great position to split England. I get Liverpool and you get London and Edinburg. I get control of the seas though. No more than the two German fleets already in existence. What do you say? It beats Russia getting Edinburgh, and it leaves us both at seven. We'd then be able to mount an assault on Russia. Me from the north and you from the midlands.
4 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Well, there's nothing I can do except accept what's real. So, I agree with your offer. We split Eng 2-1 and even out. No benefit to fighting and lots to working together. What do you want to do?

intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: 12 more hours and you'll get some good thoughts from me. I'd like for us to agree to a set of moves this season so we can both see that we are indeed interested in working together long-term, so think on that a bit for now and feel free to propose some moves for this season to get the ball rolling, I'll propose some moves myself within those 12 hours.
1 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: PS - What's the deal with Turkey? I assume you two are aligned or at least seriously considering it. I'd like to see you move on him to show you are really interested in working with me. Any thoughts on that?
2 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: Okay, I'm not seeing a whole lot that I can propose to you at the moment. It is pretty clear to me that you and the Turk are aligned, so unless you work with me against Turkey, or move against Turkey in some what, I will assume you are still against me. I think actions will speak louder than words, though I am open to ideas you may have for this season and beyond, so let me know if you have any thoughts on that front.
3 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: Hmmm, you are MUCH too quiet. You have failed another test of mine, though this time I have the time to follow up on the situation before it's too late! ;-)

In case you haven't noticed, the F/G is well on it's way, England only has two units and will be surrounded and dead very quickly. My personal opinion is the the F/G is the most powerful alliance this game has to offer, especially since it isn't as obvious as the R/T. Anyway, the longer there is chaos in the southeast, the higher the chances of the F/G taking over this game and killing all of us in the southeast, you agree with that don't you?!

My earlier statements about an Eastern Triple were 100% sincere, especially in a WTA 14,000 pot game! We need to kill off the Turk and get ready to defend against the German ASAP while Italy stalemates the Frenchman in the Med before it's too late and we all lose our 2,000 points and Ghost-rating, in my opinion.

The move to Gal was defensive when you refused to communicate earlier, but here's what I propose. Aeg hits Con to allow Italy to take Smy and build a fleet to slow down the Frenchman. Serb attacks Bul with support from Rum while Bud supports hold at Gal to see if you will work with me. If you do work with me, I will vacate Gal next season. How does that sound?

I'd ask Sev to attack Black Sea to increase the odds of me getting Bul, but I'm sure that would freak you out and send red flags for an attack on Rum. That said, I think you can convince the Turk to have Black Sea support hold at Rum (or have Black Sea support hold at Bul while Bul supports hold at Rum, though in this case Sev would be needed to hit Black Sea for me to get Bul, which I understand may be too risky for you and you'd prefer to merely see me follow through with what I say I will do first... but I trust your judgement and ability to take advantage of the Turk if you want to do so).

Anyway, to summarize. I'm really hoping we can get an Eastern Triple going. The Italian is already getting pushy about getting Greece, supposedly so he can defend against the Frenchman, but with how buddy-buddy those two's moves were last season, I have a sneaking suspicion he may have cut a deal with France and may join the F/G in a Western Triple, which is an even bigger argument for the two of us to stick together. Oops, I digressed a bit there! ANYWAY, to be clear, and to follow up on another earlier point I made and was sincere about, I'd like the two of us to agree on moves this season so we can both see we are interested in working together and surviving this game. In that spirit, here are my orders:

Bud support hold at Gal. Serb to Bul, Alb to Gre and Aeg to Con.

Again, if/when you can help get me into Bul, I will vacate Galicia and hope you will join me in advancing on the German to slow down the F/G. I will also need to defend from a possible Italian stab as his units are sort of surrounding me and he will get a build that may very well be used against me while he maintains peace with France. My hope is that a little communication (or a lot!) is all the two of us need to have a game-long alliance with the goal being surviving this huge pot game. Are you with me?! :-)
4 RUSSIA -> AUSTRIA: sorry, traveling, will be online in an hour or two

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: FYI - I think Germany is going to try to solo, beware! I got a message from England, asking if I'd support him into MAO, and he'd support me to Por because England wants to survive. Fair enough, but then Germany sends me a message saying I should consider having England go to MAO, it could help, and even though last time we talked he said he would be okay with me going to Tyrolia, he now asks if it can wait a season or two &and& wants to make sure it's okay if he can go to Gascony, etc., etc. The Germany has the Englishman in his hip pocket, England asked me to help him because England wants to survive this game, but it's not because he's offering to help me solo (which he clearly cannot offer), it's because he has already cut a deal with Germany to help the German solo. Russia may have even cut the same deal, so beware!

PS - Germany once said something to me about being afraid of you moving into Finland, that may actually be a good options at some point, the less comfortable Germany is right now, the less likely he goes for a solo and the more likely we three-way draw.

Thoughts?
1 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Those are some interesting developments. Let me mull it over. Also, I can't chat much since I'm at work now, but I'll be on later tonight.
2 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Sounds good. Germany is saying he will draw for sure, but what else is he supposed to say? I'm watching him closely, hopefully I'm just over-reacting.
3 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Overall, I still think we're in pretty good shape. We don't need to push Germany back to be on par with us, we only just need to ensure that he stays under 18 Scs.

Of course, to just hold your end of the line keeping what you currently have, you would need to get fleets into Gol, WMS, and Naf.

Worst-case would be if England and France did everything they could to help Germany solo, which in the near-term would be to help him put a power-3 attack on Spa for the fall. Hopefully, some diplomatic words can rectify this situation. Perhaps, ask Germany not to enter Gas if his intent is to merely draw. Also, England and France might be jaded enough to refuse to cooperate with Germany. How does that situation look as of now?
4 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: On my end of the line, I certainly hope that Russia hasn't made a deal with Germany to make things difficult, but I think I found a set of moves that'll work relatively safely regardless. Tyrolia is a key territory and I can force you in from Ven this Spring, but Boh and even War aren't critical, as we could also just fall back to the Tyr, Vie, Gal, Ukr, Mos line. As long as you hold your end, that would still leave us with 18 Scs combined.
5 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Germany said he'd send me a long response tonight, so we'll see. I'll ask Germany about Gas, I've already told him I don't want him there, so I will stand my ground and hope for the best. I can support myself to Tyrolia, so no worries there, you can use your units to do as you see fit.

1 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: So... I've sent Russia a message as well, though I still got no reply. I made a persuasive argument regarding attacking England and siding with Germany, but either Russia didn't read that on time or outright ignored my suggestions, as I called to the fleet to be kept.

As for moves, I'm strongly inclined to support Ion-gre and Nap-ion. Given Turkey's recent press, I'm confident I can ask for Serbia to support Alb-tri, in an apparent betrayal, which, in theory, could guarantee Budapest is not attacked with support. If you attack Serbia while I attack Greece, I suspect we can advance - Turkey can't defend both Serbia and Greece simultaneously.

What are your thoughts?
2 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Austria?
3 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: !!!
4 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Well, I'll see if I check on the game before the phase shift. In any case, I'm attacking Greece from Ionian, confident Turkey will be unprepared to defend against it and an attack on Serbia. Not only do I think this is the best moment to attack Serbia, which in theory is supporting Alb-tri, but also Albania may be disbanded if Serbia is not hit.
5 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Well, going to sleep. Fingers crossed!

0 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I've no reason to worry about you right now. There would be no logic in a quick attack against me. Yes, hypothetically I could finish off England and then turn on you with no other naval threat, and you as a smart player must consider that. But that is why I am trying to instill the good faith by not building armies. Once England is done, I am happy to turn wherever you need help. I just want to pull off some fun moves.
1 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Here's how I see it. This year, I need to take NS and NOR and get into a better position in the East. Next year, we shall see, hopefully a center there. I'll have to make a move with these three armies now. If we take down ENG in the meantime this means us two can secure a stalemate. Which might be needed if IT and AUS stick together. If they start fighting then it'll be a 3-way, with whoever makes it there.

I will try again for NS. Tell me if you need something.
2 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I think you should move Den to Ska, and Hol to NS. If NS fails, you will bounce, and you can still take Norway in the fall. If both moves are successful, then you can help me secure either Edi or Liv with cuts or support.

Your Bel army is also just sitting there. Perhaps if you get both sea, we could also think about convoying it to Norway so you can eventually use it to flank Russia to the north.

I will move to get in better protective position against an Italian attack. My next build, when it comes, will be with that in mind.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Not stabbing you wouldve worked out even worse, I think. I needed to make sure I at least got one centre from the inevitable divvying up of your empire. Admittedly, I am not in great shape now...I had expected Russia to help me.
No hard feelings?
1 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Well, you're wrong about how it would have worked out better. First off, you're not going to get that SC because I'm going to be supporting Russia into Trieste (as I warned you).

Propping me up longer would have given France and Germany a chance to come in and relieve pressure. The Russia-turkey juggernaut is on the roll, and you're next. What's worse, you've shown yourself to be totally untrustworthy. I've been communicating with France and Germany and telling them how closely we're working together, so they know that you'll sell out a close ally for just 1 SC.
2 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: I saw no signs of France or germany coming in to relieve pressure. Germany in fact told me he wasn't planning on moving east. His moves in the spring show that. it was clear to me that regardless of whether or not i retreated from Trieste, you couldn't hold off Russia and Turkey and I couldn't help you since my fleets couldnt support your primarily inland holdings. Thus, i needed to get an extra SC so that I could build a third army and stand a better chance against the juggernaut.

Its fair enough that you are helping Russia to take Trieste-- i believed your warning and i guess i expected such action. Obviously, I would rather you spend your resources slowing down the russians or the turks and I would help you in any way I could if you were doing that.
3 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: France has a big northern fleet, and that makes Scandinavia his next likely target. Meanwhile, Russia has troops on 3 sides of Germany, so he better figure it out. Notice that Germany and France both moved fleets out of England--i'm pretty sure they're on the same page.

But about us: I want to stay in the game more than I want to punish you. So if you can explain to me how that is going to happen, I'm listening. But you'll also have to tell me why I shouldn't assume you'll stab me.
4 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: I will support your serbian army into greece with F Ion and F Alb.
i will also support your [968909] army into vienna if you want, though i cant imagine that will succeed.

i won't stab you because i cant stab you...you only have centre right now, and i cant get to it. i also wont stab you because i now fully realize the strength of turkey/russia working together. before i thought i could turn russia against turkey, but ive lost faith in that.
5 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: I appreciate your offer, but it won't work...Turkey can cut your support in Ion and provide a support from either Bul or Aeg.

0 TURKEY -> AUSTRIA: So what do you think here? I should send Aegean to Ionian and Con to Aegean probably? Can you support Aegean to Ionian with Greece?

You can take Trieste back easily now. The only question is whether to let Italy take Venice, or try to keep France there. I think it's better to have Italy take it. France will want to keep it. In a year or so we can probably get you into Venice too.
1 AUSTRIA -> TURKEY: I should be able to support you through. I think you need to get towards the Wmed as quickly as possible as France is about to start bottling things up with that fleet build in Marseilles. England will be dead soon with the FG working together.

We're both at a pretty critical juncture here. I recognize the fact you're surrounding several of my dots. I think it very likely you pick up STP though if you take Mos-liv and Sev-mos. Norway will inevitably get cut by Germany in the Fall, meaning STP is yours to take from Liv.

I'll have to make a decision on covering Rumania and/or Bulgaria this season and I can't really tell you so as to discourage any stab. I'm sure you understand. :) I do think we've both got plenty of growth potential right now and in my experience, lack of growth potential should be the primary reason for a stab unless it's going to be a knockout blow. With me picking up Trieste back, there is a chance you could pick up Rumania AND Bulgaria off me, but going down one and having me turning around vs. you likely picking up STP and definitely getting Ionian seems like a bad gamble. Hopefully you're in agreement.

What do you think?
2 AUSTRIA -> TURKEY: Ionian is yours.
3 TURKEY -> AUSTRIA: Hi,

Sorry about the slow response. I agree that you should cover one of Rum or Bul. I kind of assumed you would. Even if you don't support me I might still get Ionian - it's just kind of a problem if I don't. Anyway, I don't need to know what you're doing.

Once I get Ionian we can talk about the next best move. I might need to go to West Med, but we also need to finish off Italy. I don't want to get stalemated, but I also don't want him behind me. Thankfully, he probably is less interested in working with France now.

Anyway, you know my moves. I'm going Livonia/Moscow and to Ionian and Aegean. In the fall we might want to convoy an army, but we'll see.

intent_dialogue:
0 ENGLAND -> ITALY: Any response to my suggestion? Can you help me take Paris to force Germany to play fair?
1 ITALY -> ENGLAND: Hey! I'm more than interested in keeping Germany under control, which is why I took so long to eliminate France, whom I intended to employ as a proxy for that. However, France tried to outguess Germany's moves three times even though each time I had handed Germany's planned moveset beforehand!!! Anyway, that proved way too ineffective.

I have a problem, though. While long term containing German growth is evidently a priority, it makes little sense/is somewhat unfeasible to attack Germany while Russia and Turkey are poised to tear Austria apart. I mean, directly attacking the only other power in condition to assist with armies is rather risky.

That can easily change, though. Turkey, at least on paper, seems open to an assault on Russia, as far as I have assessed. Perhaps, if you could push Turkey towards that, my situation would become easier and allow me to immediately join your forces against Germany. I'm on those talks as well, but we haven't so far reached any sort of agreement regarding the Med or even the division of Austria, as our little arms race can show.

An alternative would be talking to Russia, but I assume Russia wouldn't be willing to listen to you. Besides, has Russia even bothered to answer you recently? I can't get a single word as answer!
2 ENGLAND -> ITALY: I'm not saying "direct assault on Germany now", I only asked for a support into Paris for now. with an army alone, he cannot defend it, and he's certainly not in a position to attack Russia alone if we are united in France. I can only ask that you consider it, but he is now saying he'll only work with me if I keep North Sea as a DMZ, which seems far too trusting of me to do now that he's blatantly taken advantage of me to steal my build. He didn't even set his units in a way to advance his cause toward Russia with any greater speed, so the 3 armies looking at Burgandy would seem to indicate he thinks he can direct armies westward with no risk. We may have to fight to defend our French acquisitions soon regardless, I'm just trying to be ready early
3 ITALY -> ENGLAND: I get what you're saying, but to move one army against Germany without having further resources to bring in is tantamount to scratching a lion with a short stick, let alone when there are other two powerful land powers marching my way. So, any hostile action of my army will likely trigger a German reaction.

What makes this whole situation weird is Russia's unexpected unwillingness to answer press. Has Russia bothered to write you in the last month or so? It appears as if Turkey hijacked Russia's mind.

In other circumstances, we could perhaps work with Russia. That could settle the issue with Turkey, and allow Russia and I to contain Germany on land, despite your advances in the North. Or at least give me hope of not facing a full Jugg without Germany. As it stands, I must assume Russia will never be a partner, as s/he consistently fails to answer. I mean, no kidding, Russia answered with one line on June 6th. Since them, I sent messages on June 11th, [1643277]&, [1626053]&, [1406554]&, and short notes almost daily since then. (& denote a solid message, either elaborate or with a clear question)

With that in mind, either I have Turkey on my side or Germany, otherwise I can't contain their armies. And Turkey is an unlikely partner, especially if Russia has a solid position and Austria is gone to Turkey. However, Turkey has signalled some interest in shifting North. Can you help me make that a reality? If we can get any agreement that, provided something, Turkey will move on Russia, I can seriously consider fighting Germany.

Otherwise, I fail to see how I could survive the consequences. I'm more than eager to be convinced of the contrary, so feel invited to present your arguments!, even if I find it unlikely.
4 ENGLAND -> ITALY: Russia had been entirely silent to me until yesterday, so I just figured he was a scorned and bitter player, but all of a sudden he's also willing to cooperate with me to fight Germany, &as long as I move Stp away from him

These protracted games are so annoying. Germany will only cooperate with me if I keep North Sea DMZ forever, Russia will only work with me if I entirely retreat... with my units as far separated as they are, it seems like everyone is requesting I do nothing or retreat as a condition for working together, which is annoying. But if a Jugg smashes Germany, I'd be ok with that, as I still have the backdoor on Russia and the current army distribution means Germany is in more trouble than I am (so far). But I understand your point; perhaps Spain to Mar and Por to Spain(sc) means you can cover your gains while still being in my neighborhood?
5 ITALY -> ENGLAND: We'll find a way to settle everything alright, and cooperate to achieve our goals, even if we must not be as direct as we'd like.

For now (I hope to write you again before moves, more in depth), I strongly encourage you to bounce me in Mao! This will allow us to delay anything happening in the West, while keeping Germany under the illusion that I'm working against you.

intent_dialogue:
0 TURKEY -> ITALY: I'm sure the fleet looks threatening, but I don't plan to head past ionian if you don't involve yourself east of it. I just don't think I can afford Russia collapsing in the north while Germany does so well and England is looking like a loyal ally of G's.

Plus Austria is still being pretty belligerent and making any negotiation start with me ceding Serbia and any claim in Greece, which is an understandable stance but trying to negotiate from a position of strength doesn't endear him or seem promising for being able to hurry the hatchet.
1 TURKEY -> ITALY: His& trying to negotiate from a position of strength I mean.
2 ITALY -> TURKEY: Sorry about not replying the last message, I simply forgot it. Though I must say it was a well written one. In fact, your messages are consistently the best on the board. It must be somewhat hellish to be the most talkative player around and be stuck with Turkey.

Anyway, regarding the fleet. I appreciate your explanation, and I understand your discomfort with Austria's rather unjustified stance. I can certainly engage Austria in accepting an unequal peace settlement, but let us settle some things first.

How exactly do you plan to employ your three fleets, if not to break through Ionian? What would you look after, and how could you possibly arrange them so that they're not a clear an constant threat to my most vital position?
3 ITALY -> TURKEY: Regarding Austria,Germany and Russia, (the message was sent incomplete due to some random choice process. For some reason I entered 'send' instead of enter. Anyway) I understand Russia might fall apart if England pushes in, but right now I'd say Germany is the one at pains. I mean, thanks to some inadequate orders last season, Russia can conceivably take Munich in the Spring. Who knows what may happen then?

But, more importantly, regarding Austria... While I get your frustration, and would likely behave just as you're doing, in trying to guarantee a favourable peace settlement, suited to the circumstances, I can also understand why Austria would be reluctant to accept one.

Not the terms. I'm complete agreement with you that anything agreed with Austria must take in account the positions you now command. But, even if I were to persuade Austria of that, how is Austria to trust you actually intend to move against Russia? As it stands, anyone with minimum knowledge of the rules would look at the board and assume you to be headed against Austria and against me.

Why, and how, would Austria believe otherwise?

If we can answer these questions, I'm more than eager to work towards ever-elusive peace in the Balkans!

0 TURKEY -> GERMANY: Hey, France's builds look pretty good for you.
1 GERMANY -> TURKEY: Yep. Russia, however, is giving up on the north and persisting in the south, which is bad for me and, I presume, for you as well.
2 TURKEY -> GERMANY: Yeah, it looks to slow us up a bit. He could have been more cooperative, but after all I did just stab him...
3 GERMANY -> TURKEY: You can't have your cake and eat it, they say. But then again, why have a cake if not to eat it?

I forgot where I was going with this.
4 TURKEY -> GERMANY: You were going to share some of your famous Black Forest Cake with the Russians until they abandoned the northern front. As Russia put it to me: "I will die fighting you... no matter what happen in the rest of the map." So provided I can survive his suicide-bombing, save me a slice, would you?
5 GERMANY -> TURKEY: Sure thing.

0 ENGLAND -> TURKEY: Hi!
Austria tells me that you two are in good relationship. If you sticks together you can stop France, i think. You should conquer Russia and Germany quickly, so you can reach the 3 way draw.
To tell the truth I'm a little bit afraid that you plan to stab Austria. That way you would get into a similar good position as France has now. Because of this I plan to help a little bit France. I think if you afraid more from a France solo, it is less likely that you turns against Austria.
Of course when I will see you can't stop France without me, I will turn against him, of course only then if I would still have any unit then. :)))
1 TURKEY -> ENGLAND: You believe him when he promised to support you into Holland, then? Well, you never know. It may be true. Sadly I'm in no position to offer an alternative, so you must of course do whatever may help you survive in the immediate future.

If you manage to pull it off I'll look forward to working with you :)
2 ENGLAND -> TURKEY: No-no, he asked me to support him into Hol. I will do that now. I know that it is a dangerous movement, but I think I need to make the 3 way draw closer. For this we should eliminate Russia and Germany. I hope he won't take Lon and this way I will have one more turn to make him weaker if something turns wrong.
Survival means for me nothing, I'm playing here to help reach the draw.
3 TURKEY -> ENGLAND: The question one has to ask yourself is why wouldn't he take London? Why risk a random element such as yourself when it can be so easily replaced with a French unit under complete control?

I'm not one to tell others what to do, but I have to admit that in your shoes I'd have been more tempted to ask for German support to Denmark. He's desperate enough to need you, and it puts your unit closer to a potential stalemate line position.

Still, time will tell. Good luck!

4 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: Considering that I am unsure which way you will lean
5 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: Happy to discuss

okay, for the southern portion on land, please move exactly like this, and you will be back into Munich.

Holland to Ruhr
Silesia to Munich, supported by Berlin and Tyrolia.

5 AUSTRIA -> TURKEY: if France gets into Prussia and Livonia, we cannot defend Munich or Berlin anymore.

intent_dialogue:
0 RUSSIA -> ENGLAND: Well, you leave me with little choice in keeping defense in the north. If I leave Liv or Mos, that presents an opportunity for you to slip in. But! If we now follow our agreement of trading St. Pete for Swe, we can start semi-demilitarizing the area, meaning that I don't think either of us will completely trust the other immediately, but we can move Livonia and Barents out to more useful endeavors. What do you think?
1 ENGLAND -> RUSSIA: That depends on where Warsaw is going.
2 RUSSIA -> ENGLAND: Warsaw was going to help defend Germany, which I think was pretty obvious and nothing I can easily cover up, especially if I moved to Silesia this turn. Does this affect your ability to trade Scs? ~N~ ~N~ I hope you don't plan on convoying to Norway. Really, [1084968], packing Scand full of armies won't help since ultimately St. Pete is a roadblock. I would recommend convoying to Hol since you lack armies on the mainland. I think we are in similar positions: we're afraid of the other getting builds and using those builds against one another. Because at this moment we're mostly even in the north, though you have the upper hand. ~N~ ~N~ So, what do you want to happen?
3 ENGLAND -> RUSSIA: The problem is your support of Germany. If you help his holds, you are taking away my area to expand. If you want me to stab France, I need to finish Germany first, and take away the chance of him recovering. ~N~ ~N~ As for armies in the north, they like hanging out there, especially when Norway is so open.
4 RUSSIA -> ENGLAND: Norway isn't in danger. I have one unit, with which I have no hope of keeping Sweden and Norway. ~N~ ~N~ In order for me to not defend Germany, I need some sort of assurance or indication that you plan on stabbing France after destroying Germany. Right now it definitely seems more like you're preparing to attack me next, so I want to maintain Germany as a buffer. Convoying to Norway would only continue the indications that you plan on attacking me next and thus I need to defend Germany. If you want me to back off or even help take down Germany, show me that it will benefit me.
5 ENGLAND -> RUSSIA: I could also go south towards Austria rather than move on you. It still comes down to trust, and while you certainly have more to lose with me in the north, I have more to lose by stabbing France while you are allied with Austria.

intent_dialogue:
0 TURKEY -> AUSTRIA: I'm willing to call it between us in the interest of the west starting to become a pressing concern with EG still cooperating so closely. What would that look like/require from your side of the table?
1 AUSTRIA -> TURKEY: Very much what you might think. I at the very least require Serbia back, I am unwilling to play the role of puppet state which will be quickly disposed of later. I think that is a reasonable request for co-operation and if you do not agree I will of course continue fighting you. I do believe it may be necessary to face E/G though, so I'm willing to work with you.
2 TURKEY -> AUSTRIA: So pull out of Serbia, but what would the actual cooperation look like? Would you also make peace with Russia, or you'd expect me to go north through him with your help for us to hit EG?
3 AUSTRIA -> TURKEY: I would be happy with either. Russia is getting severely weakened in the north, but on the other hand they are the only one of us currently in the north on the front lines. If you begin pulling back from my borders I can start moving units into Bohemia, Tyrolia, Galicia(?) and form a line there. To be honest you can't do much directly without going straight through Russia to get there, which is not necessarily a good idea.
4 TURKEY -> AUSTRIA: I agree Russia is important to keep as strong as possible of a front up in the north.

Sorry about how late a reply this is as well, I wasn't trying to drop this on you last minute and I still think figuring out how we could work together is something worth doing over the next couple seasons. But I don't think it's going to happen just yet.

I just got very slow replies from Italy and Russia this turn though, and I think Italy is also an important part of the front line so I'm trying to avoid fighting him. The consensus seemed to be from Russia that it's more of a 'use his centers' vibe than a 'work with austria' plan. Maybe I'm being misled, but they seem more mission critical and selfishly otherwise I have nothing to do so I'll admit I probably didn't argue against it as well as I could have.

3 AUSTRIA -> FRANCE: Btw, wanted to check to see what is going on in the North with you and England? Seems like Germany is attacking England now?
4 FRANCE -> AUSTRIA: Yes, if I were Turkey there would be no reason to stab now while he is picking up other centers in Italy and Russia. The worry comes later, but you know that.
5 FRANCE -> AUSTRIA: Yes I appear to have turned Germany to my side.

0 ITALY -> FRANCE: I know you said you don't have a bunch of time, and may be happy to be out of this game, but thought I'd just check with you to see if you are interested in a little experiment. It's working title is Help Italy Solo, but there's another version very similar to mine that's called See If You Can Get Italy On The Verge Of A Solo And Then Screw Him Over For Spite And/Or Try To Get On A Stalemate Line For A Draw. Both titles are very good, and I'll let you decide in the end what to call it, and you can even think on it for quite some time!! :)

Anyway, My guess is that Cly and Iri will bounce in Lvp. My first request would be that you take MAO to NAO while Por moves to MAO, Spain goes to Mar and Lyo goes to Spain. SO, if you take NAO, you live on, in whatever capacity you choose, but if you don't, Por won't take MAO and you die. I think it sounds like an interesting experiment, but my opinion is pretty meaningless, so let me know what you think, it would be fun and I think we'd both learn a thing or two &and& you can call it quits at any time... Please do give it your full consideration, it should be a learning experience at the least.

PS - Please don't tell anyone anything we discuss, or if you are bitter with me and want to insure this game immediately ends in a three-way CPA, you can tell others, I don't really have much to lose, so it's your call! ;)
1 ITALY -> FRANCE: PPS - Don't get me wrong, I'm all about getting revenge... So, maybe you want to get a bit of revenge against Germany?!?! :)
2 FRANCE -> ITALY: Yeah, the name of my current plan was "make sure Germany doesn't solo". I'll consider moving to MAO
3 ITALY -> FRANCE: Hey, you are in MAO, you'd need to move to NAO! Plus, you can't win if you are dead, you can't even draw when dead. I'm sure you will get other offers to consider, the longer you live, so you could give it a go for one year, even if your only goal is to totally freak the German out, he will &lose it&, guaranteed!

Anyway, I'm a 100% revenge sort of guy, the person that I am most "bitter" with, I'll do anything/everything in my power to take them down, or at least put their demise in motion, I don't ever want anyone to ever think they can stab me and live to tell the tale, but I digress.

How about you update the order to attack NAO and sleep on it? If you don't attack NAO, you are virtually locking in a three-way and thus rewarding the German for how he's treated you in this game, which I hope you find even half as unacceptable as I do (though in a "fun", it's just part of the game, sort of thing, I'm not actually a raging lunatic, it's all in the spirit of war)!! :)

0 FRANCE -> TURKEY: Hi Turkey,

You have done well, taking Gre and having good prospects at Ser. At the same time, the A Con build leaves you with flexibility to convoy an army to the east side whenever that would be necessary.

Any news on the above? I will send a fleet south from Mar, and my army in Por will move east. Apart from that, [784237] and armies will stay around the northwestern borders I presently have with England and Germany.

What about you?

Kind regards,
France
1 TURKEY -> FRANCE: Sorry, been travelling for the last day or so.

You're planning on avoiding committing to either Russia or Germany, then? I'm a little surprised
2 FRANCE -> TURKEY: Not saying that. It also depends on you in particular. We can take out Austria together, while focusing elsewhere, but if you attack Russia i should also ensure he is attacked. So I have presently left my options open is what I wanted to say.
3 FRANCE -> TURKEY: One of the things that does not make sense is you attacking Russia while I attack Germany. They should fight as well, otherwise it will be more difficult. Which is why I'd need some direction at a given stage and feel obliged to adopt a wait and see approach until then. Happy to hear your thoughts!
4 TURKEY -> FRANCE: I'm free and easy. It probably makes more sense from a purest point of view to attack Russia now, but that must be balanced against the fact that Austria is such an arse...
5 FRANCE -> TURKEY: On the last point apparently the entire board agrees:-)

If I were you I would first take Serbia and attack Russia when also Germany is entangled in a fight with him and/or when you and I can deal with Austria together.

intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> FRANCE: im afraid not. im sorry i had to help england move into ruhr that turn, i really wanted his army away from berlin.
1 AUSTRIA -> FRANCE: but if it looks like you are beating him i will join in. my first mission is to ger berlin and finish off italy.
2 FRANCE -> AUSTRIA: I understand you want Berlin, and by all means, take it- pooor Russia can't hold out much longer, and better you should have it than England. ~N~ ~N~ That's really the theme here. England has 9 centers, you 8, the Turks 7. I'm essentially 5 centers up for grabs here, a swing state, if you will. England takes me over, he has 14, and can take on you and Turkey without heed; even if you or Turkey has an alliance with him, the odds are still against you. Not only does England stab her allies whenever she wants to (Germany and I are proof of that, a "Western Triangle Alliance" becoming an English Empire), but if I go, England and has you enclosed and quite probably flanked. You can take Italy, but that will still leave you enclosed, and England can then just filter in his massive navy into your Med. and all the way up the Adriatic; it'd take you and Turkey staying together to put up any sort of resistance, and, again, even then it would be a long drawn out war, and could very well end in England grinding you down (you WOULD be first in the way of his hurricane of fleets, Turkey'd have a bit more shelter, you're right there.) ~N~ ~N~ That fleet in the MAO sparked a war between England and I as he violated my waters (when I left HIS EC alone.) That fleet in the Western Med is undoubtably there to help take Spain- but it won't stop there, and it won't be the only Engish ship in the area soon.... ~N~ ~N~ I want to survive right now, not win. YOU can have Marseilles and the land that would otherwise be conquered by England. All I ask is that I keep either Paris or Portugal, and that you stop England before he wipes out everyone and gets away with his treachery.
3 AUSTRIA -> FRANCE: i will not let england win. well..i will try my hardest to stop him!
4 FRANCE -> AUSTRIA: Then let's attack HIM: I'll support you along the line there, to Ruhr, Belgium, Holland, Kiel- get those, and there's an instant threat on England's doorstep. That means he has to fight for it, which less pressure on you, certainly not as large of a force in the Soth for England. ~N~ ~N~ And maybe I'll survive the day. ;) ~N~ ~N~ What do you say- take Berlin and have me help you into the Rurh and beyond?

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Well, I'm glad England stabbed you, to break up the EF coming at me, but I prefer allies that do not stab so I'm hoping this is the start of something good for you and me!!

Yeah, Holland looks like an easy target, what's the plan after that? Have you made any deals with Italy, agreed on peace and that you'll be shifting at England? Have you reached out to Russia, asked him to attack Norway since England may shift units around this spring? Any other thoughts?
1 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Yep, Holland is totally unprotected. I don't think he expected Den - Nth. I guess he could move Holland - Belgium, so I'd appreciate you not tapping Burgundy and cutting Belgium's support.

I believe I have covered all the bases with respect to communicating with the other powers. However, I haven't gotten a lot of replies back. People are not very communicative in this game.
2 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Yeah, I'm pretty disappointed in how little communication there is in here, but suppose we can't change that now. Anyway, hopefully you and I will at least be communicative, I know I'll hold up my end of that bargain, and my guess is that you will too.

So, I am not attacking Bur. England has told me that EC will support Holland to Belgium, so you should be just fine with Bur supporting hold at Bel, and you could get into Irish Sea if you really want to be a thorn in his side, but that's your call! =)

The only way I can see is by attacking Sev From Rum.
1 TURKEY -> AUSTRIA: I am game, provided that we can still keep the SC count between us decent
I will support you in from the BS and Armenia. Let me know what you want from Bulgaria
2 AUSTRIA -> TURKEY: Hi
Sorry for this late message,
I understand your concern, We can postpone the Attack in Sev from rum until autumn only if we can not do differently, I will let you take Rum with Bul is so.
I would like to try to outflank Russia and if it succeeds it will give us more options in autumn, specially for you to take Sev .

if you agree how about
Galicia->Sil
Bud or Vien -> Gal
Ankara->Sev S Arm and Rum
BS conv Ankara->Sev
Bul S Rum
3 TURKEY -> AUSTRIA: I was thinking that we should stick to Rumania moving into Sev... Its the only sure way to get it
Afterwards in autumn, we could do something where you get support into Ukraine while I take Sev., or we could even do that Greece trade that we discussed earlier

My orders as of right now have Armenia and BS supporting Rumania into Sevastopol, Bulgaria holding.

There are still 7 hours on the clock, so hopefully you will see this in time (please confirm if you do)
I have no problem with supporting you in, as I think the defeat of our enemies has higher priority over who gets what countries. We can decide that when the gunfire dies down
4 AUSTRIA -> TURKEY: The flaw in this set of order (only if done in spring), it's that it let Rum empty since I need Bud,Gal and Vie elsewhere next turn.
If you move Bul in Rum to fill the gap and you attack in Sev succeeds in autumn, I could be in a situation where i will loose one unit (and you win 2 :-) ) if things don't turn out the right way for me.

In my prev msg i was just trying to say to delay only 1 turn this attack giving me time to take position around War. There no possibility for Russia to avoid this attack niether in spring nor in autumn.

0 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: I am thinking about playing for a three-way draw with you and France. I have not mentioned it to France yet, but I do think that he is cooperating against England. I figure 2-3 more game years to eliminate Italy, England & Germany. Interested? Or would you prefer to keep options open (4-way or race to solo)?
1 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: A draw sounds like a good idea to me. I have to admit I am feeling a touch nervous about being the smallest (though most easily defended, I guess?) member of that proposed finishing group.
2 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: You should pick up 2-3 Italian centers ... depending on what we do with Trieste/Venice. That should help. Of course, it is hard to say how things will go in the north. If England and Germany team up to make life hard for me, France could easily grow to 12 or so and use the builds to compete for some Italian centers (or push against me in the north). The reason I am proposing this to you instead of to France first is that (a) I think any dreams I may have had of a solo are too optimistic, and (b) you and I have developed a solid basis for trust. That means we can both devote most of our energy outwards and "convince" France that a draw is a better option than him pursuing a solo. Maybe.
3 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: I guess we will see. It really depends on what England does. I would guess he goes out like most people in this situation -- uncertain and divided.

0 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: Well, I'm not saying that it's a rational plan by Italy, but what other hypothesis would better explain his tactics and diplomacy from last season.

My guess is that he is a bit dissatisfied settling for the 3-way draw and is looking to establish a chance to either solo or at least remove me from the game.

I think he was hoping that I would have made an aggressive move on you, leaving myself more exposed for a stab that he was trying to line up for the fall. He was acting all paranoid about you and was trying awfully hard to convince me that you would attempt to solo, how [659259] all might try to help you solo, and all that nonsense. He was even trying to persuade me to move into Finland. I imagine that he tried to persuade the opposite (that I would try to enter Finland) to you?
1 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: So, Italy is still telling me that his only interests with his past and future moves are to prevent you from soloing and to establish the 3-way draw. Frankly, I don't really believe that. I think his Spring moves were intended to set up for an opportunistic stab, should he elect to follow through this fall with the intent to remove me from the game for either a solo attempt or to work toward a 2-way. He &might& be thinking of backing out of that plan now, since perhaps I didn't leave myself as wide open as he expected I might, but I really can't be too sure of his intent. His forced move on Bulgaria was perhaps intended to destroy that army (if I had self-bounced in Ser), and he was perhaps hoping that I would have overextended away from Trieste leaving that home SC open to be snatched by Tyrolia and Venice.

This fall, Italy will either follow through with the stab or he won't.

Hopefully, he'll abandon the stab, backing out of Bulgaria and moving away from my Scs. That would allow the two of us to set up and hold one of several stalemate lines that would insure that we keep 17 Scs and force the 3-way draw.

However, if Italy continues with the stab, it can only be with the intent to see me out of the game through either an Italian solo or 2-way IG draw. If that is what he chooses, I would do everything I can to throw the solo to you. So, to prepare for that contingency, I would like you to take Stp and Warsaw away from me this fall, and to also attack Tyrolia from Munich. If Italy doesn't stab me, we would still be in position to ensure the stalemate. However, if Italy does stab me and tries to press for the solo, I want you to be in position to capitalize on me throwing the solo to you.

I am doing this on a matter of principle. I've done my best to explain this situation to Italy. So, if Italy is stupid enough to throw away an easy 3-way draw position for the insane ambition of attempting a solo at my expense, he needs to be punished with a German solo. Even if his moves is actually the result of some incredible manipulation on your part, possibly including the promise of giving him a 2-way draw, he still needs to be punished with seeing you solo, and intend to ensure that this game won't end in a two-way draw.

Well, I really hope that it doesn't have to come down to this contingency, but I just wanted to let you know what I am prepared to do.
2 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: i can certainly assure you that I don't believe in [1410949] draws. and i have not had any conversation with italy regarding that. my take is that he wants to try for a solo himself, or as you said, set himself up for the attempt.

I feel hesitant to try to take war from you. are you sure you want me to try to do that? i can take stp and i can hit tyrolia, but I am really not interested in being in such a position that then I become the solo threat and end up helping italy get into the atlantic in some fashion.

I have told him very clearly that if he goes to MAO, that I will do all in my power to stop him as well and will consider us at war. so hopefully we have both given him a strong enough message that he does not make such an attempt.

but suffice to say that if he does continue down this path, I'll be there to back you up 100% and will help in any way I can.

Give me a few more details and I'll give you an honest answer, but for now, I'm with you 100%, as well as with the CPA 100%. I'm confident England is trying to replace you in that three-way draw scenario, so be careful, the guy is crafty.

intent_dialogue:
0 FRANCE -> GERMANY: Here's what I propose: Let me move Ven back to Pie. You support yourself to Ven. I have a unit to spare, so that won't hurt me. Hold off on taking London for this turn, and take it next year. In the meantime, I can work my army back to Paris, as per our exchange, and then England will be dead so I can move my fleets south while you take those centers.
1 GERMANY -> FRANCE: ?This makes no sense?

Ok, I guess the others talked a lot. But let's go through this one by one:
1. Why move back to PIE? You will place in MAR anyway next turn and can then go back to take PAR and BRE? This is a full retreat and you're giving them a center. I cannot support myself to VEN alone - it's 2 vs. 3 if TRI helps.

2. You don't want me to take LON, but are ok to lose another center? Come on, you can't expect me to be ok with this in any way. What is the point? I don't want to lie to you, I'm moving as I told you - GAS-BUR, BUR-MUN, NS-LON, HOL-NS with support from NOR. I am in a position where I really think I don't need to lie to you.

3. Look, my main objective for this game was to make up for missing game 1. I can achieve this with a 3-way or 2-way draw also. I know that getting a solo will have implications, it always does...

Anyway, my point is simple - I have a stalemate line against the East. They can't do anything to me, nor can they help you in any way. I don't want to fight you, as this will only lead me to a draw. However, we need to keep pushing east.

For all practical purposes if you control the Mediterranean you can always stalemate me there, so you will hold me hostage if I decide to attack you in full.

It is in your interest to take Italy, I am not joking about this. Look at the map and you will see that this will give you value and power that you do not have currently against me. If we fight now you'll die, and I have a good shot at finding other allies on similar terms, a lot of people are desperate in this situation.

I am really not ok with retreating from Italy. This will be a huge mistake and you're not doing yourself a favor. TUN and VEN are exactly the reason I am interested in working with you, otherwise I would have accepted AUS/It's offer of a 3-way draw a long time ago.

I'd strongly suggest that you stick with me on this one. Unless I'm missing something it will be plain wrong to go against me at this point. I have no problem with you planning for your 'independence', it's only normal, but let's be smart and not lose the game over it.
2 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I'm not losing the game over it. The retreat from Ven was not a proposition to go against you. You have a glut of armies, and if you are indeed moving out, you will have enough to take Italy. I was not thinking about a build...poor calculations on my part. Like I said before, I look at this map for about 5 minutes a day. I'm far from in form here.

Obviously I lose if I fight you. I'm not thick. But you are nearly accusing me of turning against you, when all actions I have done have been in support of you. You moved into my homeland, and I supported you. You then took my home centers against my wishes, and I supported you. You then moved south which serves no purpose but to launch at attack on Spain and Mar, and now I am the one who is being called into question for raising some minor concerns about my remaining centers? At what point did that sound like me attacking you?

I have fleets all over the Med that over power all others. I have no means of opposing you on land. Please stop threatening me with ultimatums. You don't want me to move to Pie? Fine. I will take your support to Rome. You take London, I take Edi, I build in Mar, I take back my centers.

Watch. This is me trusting you again. Again. And again. If I were judging by past moves, one would assume that Mar will be gone next turn. But this is my attempt again to prove myself wrong. Let's see what happens.
3 GERMANY -> FRANCE: Sorry if I was too harsh. I have no issue with anything you've done so far and know you've done nothing against me the whole game. I just reacted like this because what you suggested was not optimal and it sounded like an ultimatum itself - I couldn't just agree to it.

As for you trusting me - I know I cannot expect this from you - so I'm asking you to trust me, I am trying to explain how I see things, so that we can reach a logical conclusion and move in a way that is constructive for both. Forget the trust, let's approach this more pragmatically.

I have pushed the others into the corner without any ability to react, you can go all the way to TUR and we can eliminate everyone else if they don't get organized soon. They way things are going this may very well end up as a 2-way draw.

0 ITALY -> TURKEY: LOL, I told Austria if he didn't waive his build I would make sure he dies even if I die along with him, guess he believed me!! ;)

Anyway, I think I need to convoy Tunis back to Apu for extra defense, don't you? If East Med attacks Aeg, then I'd even have the option of convoying that army to Greece this fall. What do you think?
1 TURKEY -> ITALY: That would be fine with me, but what makes you think you could get into Greece?
2 ITALY -> TURKEY: If I convoy to Apu this spring, then Ion could convoy to Greece with support of Aeg in the fall, depending on how things go in the spring. It would give me security to convoy to Apu this springk, yet not totally handicap me by providing an option of doing something in the fall. Not sure that makes as much sense in my head as it does me explaining it, or does it make sense to you now too?
3 TURKEY -> ITALY: It makes sense, what I'm saying is that he may verywell support Greece with Serbia.
4 ITALY -> TURKEY: Yeah, but he may not, you never know if you don't try! Anyway, my top priority is defending my home centers and Tunis isn't doing anything to help at the moment, and I don't see France coming my way any time soon. Would you suggest I do something else this turn? I'm open to ideas. With Trieste open, I will keep Venice this year if I attack Tyrolia, so that Austria can't get into both Tyrolia and Trieste, so that is of much comfort, but a second army will give me even more security. Plus, if I need that army at home, I can always send a fleet at Greece, it'd just be nice if I actually got Greece to have the Ionian fleet to then defend it.

If you have any other thoughts for me, please shoot them my way. If Austria does not come at me, and I do take Tyrolia, then I could use Tyrolia to support Apu to Ven in the fall, so that's a plus as well, I'll have options.
5 TURKEY -> ITALY: No, that sounds solid to me.

0 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: I am sorry for some reasons I got your message just now.
I apologize for being rude and not answering your press.
To respond to your enquiry, I never agreed to leave the EC empty, except the very first time when you took advantage of this, and there is no need to say here how many times you said something and you did the opposite instead.
I offered you another deal, which is still on, I will push my fleet from Brest to EC, as a sort of insurance, than i will move the fleet from Iris sea to MAO.

Anyway i heard about You and Russia taking Den, as the Russian offered me to be part of the Germany take over it seems we are again on the same side.
1 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: Yes, indeed. Let's work on the same side. What's done is done. Fall back to MAO and begin your conquest of the Med. You have my word that if I break the deal by moving into EC again then our deal is off permanently. Sound good?
2 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: No. I am sorry
3 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: You want to be on the same side, but you want to tie up our fleets bouncing in EC and keep me penned in Lvp?

Or, you want to be on the same side, but only if you occupy EC?
4 FRANCE -> ENGLAND: No. I am sorry
5 ENGLAND -> FRANCE: I asked two separate questions there, sir. Let me recap my understanding.

1. You want to be on the same side.
2. You want to occupy the EC with a French fleet as well as MAO, leaving Irish Sea open.

If I yield the EC to you then will that satisfy your conditions?

intent_dialogue:
0 GERMANY -> FRANCE: So, was that Belgium quote because you wanted to know if I'm mad that you took Munich? I'm ok with that, if I keep Belgium for now at least.

I'm guessing what you had worked out with England and Italy was a sort of stop-the-leaders style thing? Because I'm ok with that. If we do this for a couple years, then turn back around on England, I think that would be a pretty great deal. But if it gets so bad that I have to start disbanding fleets, you're going to lose out on your opportunity to strike at England.
1 FRANCE -> GERMANY: I'm impressed that you don't react with some sort of Holy War response.

In truth, I was worried about your veracity. I couldn't understand your taking of Belgium after you said otherwise, and your offer to hold Burgundy sent alarm bells ringing. The rate at which Austria is going is the real problem. Turkey is not putting up a sensible defense, so with no Russia, the situation was getting untenable.

More later...
2 FRANCE -> GERMANY: We will need to have a serious talk about the future after the builds. You'll have to be very straight-forward though.
3 GERMANY -> FRANCE: I promise the Belgium thing was an accident! I had the order to move to Belgium before you told me not to, and I thought I changed it. Not that that matters anymore, really.

I have no idea what Turkey is doing. I'm ostensibly working with him (me taking Warsaw was crucial to his survival... I thought). The plan was that, if Austria didn't get another fleet build, and Italy didn't send fleets to help, then Turkey could turtle forever. But now Turkey is screwing everything up. I really hope that he just puts in a lot of support hold orders from now on.
4 GERMANY -> FRANCE: But yeah, let's talk more after the builds.
