intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> ENGLAND: You have a very interesting position. As long as France stays on your side, it's quite tenable. However, if France should turn on you, you will crumble very quickly, and France is almost at the point where he doesn't need you any more. Disbanding gas tells me that you're going to focus on your northern front. Is there anything I can do to help you?

The Russians keep telling me that if I don't change sides in the south, you're going to win the game in a few years. I myself don't find this argument terribly persuasive, and in any case, I'd rather have a powerful, honest, England than a powerful, dishonest, Russia.

Do you talk much to Turkey? I find his builds encouraging; do you think our little three-way deal will continue to work out?
1 ENGLAND -> AUSTRIA: What you can do to help me is to keep the pressure on Russia! Russia is talking me up to get the spotlight off of himself. Turkey is relatively quiet, but what he does say you can take to the bank. I'm optimistic our three-way will hold up, but cautiously so, once you start to take something for granted in this game it will certainly bite you in the ass.
2 AUSTRIA -> ENGLAND: Yeah Russia is offering me the world in an oyster if I turn on Turkey. I'm sure he's offering you something similar. He's about as trustworthy as Italy, and deserves the same fate.
3 ENGLAND -> AUSTRIA: Cheers to that! ;)
4 AUSTRIA -> ENGLAND: Has Germany or Turkey said anything recently?

intent_dialogue:
0 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: Excellent! That is a big destroy for us. Looks like Germany and Italy are working together to build an eastern front, but I think we can match them. Have you talked to France at all about what he might do once he's mopped up Italy?
1 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: England&, I mean
2 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Yes, that turn went beautifully. We can certainly hold the south perfectly fine, he cannot break through into Bulgaria or the Aegean until he works his way into Budapest then Rumania. Unfortunately he can break through into those.

Would you mind if I moved into Constantinople? It would get me a build in the north where we really need it (if I can hang onto Vienna) or mitigate my losses if I don't. Down the road it can help in the Med if we can break through Italy, or you can force it out of its spot and I can disband it in favor of an army in the north. I know it is alot to ask, but I will get overrun by Germany/Italy without more units.

Also, I did reach out to France and he was considering turning on Germany, but I'm not sure we can count on him doing anything this turn.
3 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: If you absolutely need to borrow a center then that's fine with me. The plan I propose would be: you move into Con, use your build to take a northern center. Once you've picked up that build we should disband your southern fleet so you can pick up another build in the north and really press your advantage. I can't advance much at the moment until pressure on the north end of Italy's line or a French expedition in the Med leaves Serbia vulnerable, so I will just hold my ground.
4 RUSSIA -> TURKEY: Sounds good. Rumania will continue to hold Bulgaria and I'll be doing my best to make some progress in the north. If you can do anything to try to convince France to move into action, go for it.
5 TURKEY -> RUSSIA: I've reached out but haven't heard back yet. Will keep you posted.

It wouldn't hurt to have a little insurance. If you help me into Tyrolia I could support you to Trieste in Fall if it turns out that's what you want to do.

What do you think?
2 ITALY -> FRANCE: I don't really know what to do at this point. I'm not going to get very far in Turkey, and I'm doubting I would even get into Trieste if that were the case. Do you have any suggestions? Because at this point I am sitting here doing absolutely nothing.
3 FRANCE -> ITALY: Ah the perils of playing Italy!

I guess it comes down to whether you think Austria is on your side or not.

If you think he is, then keep putting the pressure on Turkey, and pressure Austria to attack Turkey, and help you.

On the other hand, if you think Austria is against you, or, most likely, just using you until he finds it convenient, then you could attack him pretty effectively with Syria - Albania, and supporting me to Tyrolia. Turkey would probably be quite relieved. And, just in case, you'd still have the option to go after Greece and stick with Austria.
4 ITALY -> FRANCE: I'll see how the next turn goes. I do think Austria is being truthful. I spoke to Turkey, but I doubt they'll get a chance to respond before the turn is up.

intent_dialogue:
0 FRANCE -> TURKEY: Hi Turkey. You have done well. With Ser and Gre open, a superpower Turkey may be rising after this or next year. Let me know if I can be of any help.
1 TURKEY -> FRANCE: A friendly fleet worrying the Italian is always useful. No need to actually do anything other than build it in Marseille and let it look threatening. A bit of gunboat diplomacy in its truest form :).

Oh, it would be useful to know your intentions. Most French players in your situation will quite happily spend a year or two utterly focused on England to avoid making a decision on what to do next, but I rather suspect you're somewhat more proactive.
2 FRANCE -> TURKEY: I still have to decide my future plan actually. After England, there are only two options really and both are interesting for different reasons. It would also help here to know what your intention is. Want to stick with Russia for a while or do you intend to break that alliance up in the near future?

This would impact the game given that RT staying together in the near future is best served by France attacking Italy and Germany together with you both. On the other hand, if you start fighting Russia, you might be helped more by a strong Germany that can help you deal with the Tsar, and you and I can work against Italy together in the meanwhile.

All you say is under the strictest confidentiality. If you feel it is too early to decide or tell, I will be here whenever it is something you want to discuss.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> RUSSIA: I don't think I can stress how important maintaining parity is for me. It's something that's tremendously worrying. I understand your concerns regarding a balance in the East, but I'd really appreciate an overall balance, since an imbalance in the East can be corrected later on much more easily. Is that all right?

My moves this turn were completely stifled. With F Albania, though, I think we can make our devastating attack this turn. I think an attack involving you supporting me into Vienna from Tyrolia, into Serbia from Bulgaria, and into Trieste from Vienna would work. That's, of course, assuming we're both okay with SC parity. What do you think?
1 RUSSIA -> ITALY: How's this: I support you into Vienna, you take Trieste, and you hit Serbia while I take Budapest, then you take Serbia next year?
2 ITALY -> RUSSIA: That would be superb. You're not covering Warsaw, though?

I'm a bit unclear, though, are you okay with the parity thing? My maximal apologies for bringing it up yet again, but I'm still not clear as to what the resolution of the issue was, and I'd like for us to be in agreement!
3 RUSSIA -> ITALY: I'll be covering Warsaw with Silesia.
4 RUSSIA -> ITALY: I'm fine with trying to keep a relative balance in Scs, but I hope you understand my concern with all of your Scs and units being in the East while a third of my units are out in the Atlantic.
5 ITALY -> RUSSIA: I completely understand. We discussed briefly our plans for withdrawing forces after we take Austria, which is something we can hash out further and implement. After Austria, I'd like to shift my focus to the west and take out France and Germany quickly for our draw with England.

0 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: that should be manageable. i need to get into Bohemia though.... can i move to Galicia so I can support myself in next turn? you'll be able to build to protect Warsaw anyway. ~N~ ~N~ I can move Rumania to Bulgaria to ease any concerns you have about a stab. ~N~ ~N~ I'd also add that Fra/Eng are again in contact trying to persuade me to stab you, while I'm trying to do the same thing to them. In all likelihood the alliance that sticks together the longest will win the game. So i'm sticking to my guns. With Turkey out the way, we need to find a way to remove Italy without it falling into French hands. I think a convoy to Apulia will do the trick, which we can arrange once the Aegan fleet is gone next turn. (but needs to be done quickly to prevent Italy joining France).
1 RUSSIA -> AUSTRIA: Yes, you can move Bud -> Gal to support your move into Boh. Because, yes, I agree that Bohemia is a centrally important area for defense. ~N~ ~N~ Do you think Italy is leaning towards supporting France? I feel that France has been more aggressive in the past, and Italy has more reason to distrust France. A truly effective stab will be difficult in such a crowded area... I support a convoy to Apu, but not this move.
2 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: Tx for Galicia. ~N~ ~N~ I don't think Italy is leaning towards France right now... and just reviewing how it might be possible to get him out of the way and still push France back. If it's not possible then we keep him onside and all work together. Priority is still to push the French back, which i think should be possible given he only has 3 fleets..... but will require edging him back in Tyrolia first then Piedmont. Will take fair bit of time I think.
3 RUSSIA -> AUSTRIA: It will take time. I'm a bit anxious, and we will almost have to rely on missteps like France missing a turn... But it's good to know that we have Italy and Germany on our side, as small and imperfect as that might be. ~N~ ~N~ I'm going to step up attempts to persuade England to attack France. I am going to do this by trying to convince him I will participate in a double stab where North turns against South. We'll see if this works, he might be suspicious, but just to let you know in case you hear something.
4 AUSTRIA -> RUSSIA: sounds good.

intent_dialogue:
0 FRANCE -> RUSSIA: Dear Russia,

Apologies for my silence the past turn. I was rather busy in real life and figuring out where I would send my fleets. But there is no real explanation or justification for my silence.

Asking me for my opinion on Germany, I always find tricky. I will try to answer as honestly and openly as I can, but please keep this to yourself. Germany is in my opinion a skilful player. He has suceeded in claiming Swe, and ould probably also take Lon and Edi. In the meanwhile, he has also build 3 fleets already which can only be used particularly against you, or perhaps against me.

If Germany would keep Swe and take Edi plus Lon, he will be the superpower of the map under the present circumstances. You and I will be at 7 after this year is my expectation, but his positioning would exceed ours.

After England is gone, you or me will be Germany's new target. If we want to avoid or limit that risk, there is always the possibility of dealing with him together, but it also depends on your objectives.

intent_dialogue:
0 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: What I have just sent to Russia and France:

Austria and I are talking frantically with France to try and get him to stop assisting Germany to the win.

That, frankly, was the outcome I hadn't expected. I had expected F and G to be fighting, whilst, honestly, Austria and I eventually removed you two, leading to a joint alliance against one of the two bigger powers, leading to a 3 way draw with A/I and one of F and G.,

The stab by Germany, yet with France assisting, has left me gobsmacked - I never expected that, especially as, in league play, he gets no points for a second place to a win.

Austria and I now have no choice - we have to work with everyone left - you, me and him, to try and achieve a draw. France will, I think, work with us as he has said he will switch sides as long as he can guarantee particpating in a draw that leaves him surviving.

I think a blockade is workable here. Moscow and Sev support each other, Ukraine supports Warsaw, Gal supports Warsaw, Rum supports Gal, Vienna and Tyrolia support each other, Venice works with Rome, whilst Adriatic, Ionian, Mars, MAO, Tunis fleets can set up a blockade in the west.

Smyrna, Sev and Bul can take down the remains of Turkey, leading to an extra unit for Italy and Russia to assist in stalemate duties.

France, Austria, Russia and Italy work for a five way draw with Germany - eminently achievable, as the stalemate line is already there in most places.

I'm copying this to all parties - France, Austria and Russia (to who this message was originally written).

I seriously think this will work. Otherwise, we just limply hand the win to Germany, and concede defeat in the League season after just two games, as a win in the last two games is unlikely...
1 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Trying to persuade France, but it's not looking good. I'll paste you my chat to him if you want?
2 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Sure, sounds good.

The insanity of France's moves make me wonder if it's not actually an inter-game agreement (he'll throw this one for [432255], and then [432255] will do likewise in a later game). Otherwise, it just makes no sense.
3 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: I realise this - here's his press to me, then mine to him:

I admire your persistence and the attention you have given this plan. There are several problems, however, the foremost being the size of this operation. You want a grand alliance, and while it is a goal to remain in the game and have a chance at a draw, getting five players to hold together is difficult, especially when splitting between fewer players yields more points. At six centres, Austria is not so far behind that a split with Germany wouldn't be a bad thing. That is one thought.

For my personal position, Germany can would not have to do much to dispose of me. Yes, you and Austria can send your forces to assist me, but then we have a long game of defense against the German fleet, which has no one to attack but me, and I be down to just the Iberian. That this is my own fault is not lost on me, but I was trying a novel tactic which did not work.

Ultimately, and this is really my driving criteria in evaluating this, is that a five way draw is not as helpful in the long term for the league. It is not lost in the second game, as you said. [432255] is a new player, so a solo is 12 points total for him. [1038194], PB, and I think [1134393] took 3 points each last game. A five way split gives us each 2.4 points, or something like that, upping their total. Motivation wise, it make the next few games more appealing for them to group together to try for the top three spots, together, with tight competition for the forth. It's just logical, since it serves their mutual benefit. Not that I am accusing them of playing that way, but it's something I consider. I am not just letting Germany win, but I am not in the right position to strike, and I am detest playing a purely defensive game for the sake of a five way draw. If it is down to three or four of us, then that makes more sense to me.

I appreciate your efforts in trying to orchestrate the alliance, and I don't mean to be rude, since I hate to see my own plans fall through. But for the moment, I am not going to go along with it. I tell you that up front, rather than lead you on.

I sent you a very long email message and it didn't send - I'll type again, as it's worth sending.
04:55 PM Right, that didn't send properly, so here goes.

Firstly, the size isn't an issue. We are already on the stalemate line all along the eastern front down to Switzerland. The only place it is not in place is around Spain and West Med. With your fleets in Tunis, in MAO, Mars, and our fleets in Ionian/Adr, it will be easy to set up a stalemate line that will last.

If it's a long defence, so what? Key here is not to let Germany win. You say that you will benefit from letting [432255] win. This is just wrong!! Let me lay out the two tables & firstly if [432255] wins, then if we obtain a draw:

[432255] wins:

[432255] 12
TGM 4
[1038194] 4
[1052172] Bear 4
[244023] 0
[651562] 0
[1134393] 0


And if it's a draw:

TGM 6.4
[1038194] 4
[1052172] Bear 4
[432255] 2.4
[244023] 2.4
[156027] 2.4
[1134393] 2.4


In other words, if you go for the draw, you are only 4 points behind the leader, and 1.6 points behind second place. If you let Germany win, you will be 12 points behind the leader, and 4 points behind second place, on equal 4th.

Clearly, it makes sense to go for the draw, especially as 2 of the players who drew in the first game & [1038194] and [1052172] bear, will be knocked out in game 2 before a possible draw.

Yes, a five way draw isn't pretty, but it's in your and our best interests here. You can't win, so go for the draw.

Here are 5 good reasons for changing your mind:

1. Doing the stalemate line in the west is easy & we have the fleets to do it
2. Doing the stalemate line in the east is easy & it's there already
3. Germany will have a long stalemate line to defend.
4. Germany can get to 16 units (with the 3 English centres) but no further & guaranteed draw.
5. If you go for the draw, it will ensure you get points, rise up the league table, and improve your personal statistics with a draw, not a defeat.

intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Yeah, we're a little up against it here. I will certainly tell him that you need the build more, I need all the help I can get. Would you like to convoy Tunis over this turn? I doubt you'll need it there any time soon the way France is looking.
1 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: I think we got extremely lucky with timing, and with Turkish choices. Given that Spain is a sure conquest, even if Turkey does break past Ionian, I'll have three fleets to fight that next year.

As of now, my army is free to join the fight. Albania, I assume?

It has a small problem, though. We must decide our moves wisely, as you can only keep Serbia by using both armies to support hold it, while my army needs support for the move to succeed. Given that Germany seems stalemated against Russia (and unable to build), but Russia can't simultaneously defend Rumania and keep you out of Galicia, maybe we should go into the offensive?

I'll see if I set up my map later today to take a better look, but I'm certainly hoping you'll have bright ideas before that!
2 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Actually, I have a horrible idea. Trieste s Tunis-albania, Budapest s Serbia-rumania, Vienna-galicia. It can be countered if they hold Rumania and take Serbia with Albania though. However, we'll have Galicia and Albania assuming Silesia remains where it is, which means it's a [1592570] and we can take it back. Except they still have Greece, which can cut Albania. That's the worst case scenario though.

It may still be our best option though. The only other good option I can see is the double support hold.
3 ITALY -> ITALY: Ok, it seems to be all set regarding the convoy.

I had an idea, though. Do you think you can possibly persuade Russia to enter flawed orders?

I don't know how it would be best to pull that off, but our position would be even better if Serbia-rumania actually worked.
4 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: This seems like a plan! Bold, but it appears we hold the advantage even if it goes wrong, unless Russia moves the armies in Germany in your direction. But well, in that case, what can we do anyway?

I've entered the convoy to Albania!
5 AUSTRIA -> ITALY: Well I've asked Germany to attack Berlin and explained why it's important, so even if he moves those units after us it might be fine. It's a risky plan, sure, but we can't really do much without taking risks in this position.
6 ITALY -> AUSTRIA: Well, fingers crossed!

0 ITALY -> TURKEY: Well, this could be a thing, but they'd always be fleets in being anyway... Unless you'd be willing to go through the trouble of disbanding some of them?

I was figuring you'd want to send them West, in which case I'd need my own as well.

Anyway, I'd say the scenario is set. Should I expect Serbia to support Alb-tri? If so, I'll cover Venice. Other than that, it seems to me perfect timing for Russia to be in no shape to take actual advantage of Austria's dismantlement, especially if you take the opportunity to charge North as well.
1 TURKEY -> ITALY: Yes, serbia will support you to tri this turn if you are good with that. I'm ok in principle with disbanding fleets, mostly just worried about the timing it'd slow us down for heading west. But I suppost it wouldn't slow us down more than you feeling you have to match the fleets over in the east and so can't send units south.

How would you like to do that, then? EM to Ionian and then in fall tunis and naples disband it?
2 ITALY -> TURKEY: I was thinking of somehow moving West while doing this, but haven't figured these things exactly. Maybe we can do it this way, in lieu of a better idea. Hopefully, with the dismantling of Austria in good timing and the collapse of France, all will be well.
3 TURKEY -> ITALY: Ok, that sounds good! I have support for you to tri and a fleet to ionian ordered.
4 TURKEY -> ITALY: I'll support myself in if you want to bounce Aegean again and then retreat to tunis. Sorry for the late update, just looking at this before I go to bed and realized it'd be a good moveset and Greece has nothing else to do.

intent_dialogue:
0 FRANCE -> ITALY: Wow, Austria was definitely not joking when he said he wants to attack you full force.

But I think he is making a mistake. You can assure that you do not lose any unit, by tapping all his supporting units. Tun-ion, Nap-apu and Tyr-tri assure Austria can't take Nap or Ven. Only risk then is Rom, but I'd probably assure you would cover that if I were Austria.

And if you do that, you can have Ven support Tyr-tri, and who knows take Tri if you have Russia's cooperation.

No need to tell me anything on what you decide to do. Just some thoughts. Important will also be to break RT up, not now already, but definitely in the years to come.

Let me know if you want to discuss anything, also on my side. I'd be happy to hear your thoughts.
1 ITALY -> FRANCE: My biggest fear is Tri supporting Apu to Ven with Vie tapping Tyr to cut support. That'd be hard to block.

The rest is pretty easy.

Turkey is going to be a HUGE problem with so many free builds. Austria threatened to kill himself to just attack me, so I guess he's true to his word in that regard.

I don't think I'll be able to stand up to RT once they reach me since I won't be able to expand with the Austrian assault in my face.

My only hope is that I'll be able to flip one of them, but they'd be dumb to stab each other.
2 FRANCE -> ITALY: Juggernaut always falls apart at a given time, definitely in a reward-solo-only tournament. They can't get there if they let each other live. The fact that Turkey moved against Russia early on, is something you could exploit to create discord.

With the above moves Tri S Apu would be blocked, particularly by Tyr-tri cutting support.

Once RT gets to you, I could come to join and help you if they would indeed not stop and continue to grow together, although I guess that would only be a measure of last resort :-)

France would love it if you and I started fighting.
1 ITALY -> TURKEY: yes, france has been aching for that for a while. i don't understand why austria can't be the target of your ambitions. no doubt the gains in austria would make possible further expansion into russia. i can't let you through, though. a war between you and france with me in the middle would be the dumbest thing for me to allow :P
2 TURKEY -> ITALY: I can't turn on Austria until Russia is neutralised, and that's taking an annoyingly long time. Someone needs to reign France in in the meantime, especially as he's nicely set up to steamroller England.
3 TURKEY -> ITALY: Are you interested in helping us attack France yet? Because if you're not... we could cause you problems. And like I've tried to explain you're not the one we're really after!
4 TURKEY -> ITALY: France gets 2 extra builds this turn. It's decision time. Are you going to help him win this game, or help us keep it open enough so that any of us can win it?
5 ITALY -> TURKEY: look i've been trying to get along with you but all you seem to offer are empty promises. how can i believe you will not use your current position to attack me?

intent_dialogue:
0 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: So, has that stiff drink kicked in yet?! I think I can talk Italy down from this, it makes FAR too much sense for him and me to secure our southeast stalemate position and for him to shift at France to help you out while I finish Russia off and then I can help you with Scandinavia eventually... Are you still with us?!
1 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: Yes, I'm still with you. I'm going to do my best to hold strong against France and England, but it's anybody's game right now. Except Turkey's.
2 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: I wouldn't give Russia much hope either, personally!

I'd be ecstatic with a three-way draw and a middle power alliance has made all the sense in the world to me since day one, so that is my goal... Hopefully Italy will see the light and realize if he leaves France unchecked that France may very well end up with 14,000 points to his name!
3 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: So, can you imagine Ska attacking Norway? What if Mos supported Norway to Stp while Norwegian slid into Norway? Baltic could cover Swe while Kiel covers Den, Ruh covers Kiel and Sil covers Mun... This could get you to seven centers and a build! Think about it and let me know since Mos hitting Sev would be useful as well, but the highest priority is keeping you as strong as possible, which will also result in you being able to slow down the E/F as much as possible...
4 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: I am 100% aligned with a central powers alliance; France and England are, quite obviously, my biggest threats right now, and I must handle them. I'd love to take St. Pete; I can see that it would help both of us immensely, and if there's something I've learned this game, it's that you put a dying dog out of its misery. If Moscow will support Norway to St. Pete, I will move Norway to St. Pete and NWG to Norway per your suggestion. Similarly, Silesia will move to Munich to help cover my home centers. I've thought long and hard about this, and it is a great plan. I will gladly take your support into St. Pete.

France will get, at most, one build this turn, and after Italy's moves I can see that we are in a delicate situation. In the interest of equal growth, would you consider letting Italy hold onto Trieste, Smyrna and Ankara so that he can equip his western front with enough firepower to push back France? I would consider it a long-term investment in our continued viability, and a strong strategy to contain E/F. I eagerly await your response.
5 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: Great, glad you are onboard! Moscow will support you into Stp, that works for both of us as you suggest. France is a HUGE concern and I am in agreement on Italy keeping Trieste, Smy and Ank. Glad the three of us finally appear to be on the same page, I've been pushing this Central Powers alliance since day one, here's to our success!! :-)

1 FRANCE -> ITALY: Hi Italy,

Thanks for keeping press up. I took a little break from this game given I didn't need to do anything the last couple of turns and I had other things on my plate. Your messages in the meanwhile are much appreciated.

I moved to Wes to keep all options open. To block if Austria would be coming from it, to allow moving for it before Turkey or Austria could take it, and to leave my options open in term of Mao.

You once told me your centers would be better in my hands than in Austria's, which I'd kindly agree with. Do you still think that is the case? If so, could we ensure I take Tun before Austria can take it. A/T seems heading to a strong alliance so they may be better off in my hands to help get builds to fight both of them.

I am not sure what you consider, but this could be a good idea more longterm.
2 ITALY -> FRANCE: You're asking quite a lot with that. You're asking me to give up and lose here and now.

Why not keep me around? If you take Tunis, you'd have to rebuild a unit and then deploy it into the Med for it to be effective here. Why not let me operate as a puppet state for you? A fleet already in the Ionian is something you can't get for years to come.

So while one of your units would be Green, it is still in a more advanced position than you'd be able to get for a while to come.

What do you think?

0 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: You are not moving on anyone? Sure you want to tie your destiny in this game to RUS and IT?
1 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: No, and I was about to move on Italy once Smyrna fell. However, France's odd behaviour more or less ruined this.

Can you give me a reason why you wouldn't keep going for a solo at this point?
2 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: 1. Metagaming. My goal was to get a good result to compensate for missing game one. I can get this with a 2/3-way draw also. I don't want to be annihilated in the other two games, which is what will probably happen otherwise. It's just no fun.

2. I am not so close to winning. Yes, I can take out FRA and he's sided with me, but he also holds me at gun-point, as without TUN and/or Italy I can never get to 18.

3. I also feel it is right for FRA to be part of any potential draw, he's been my ally so I'd prefer to reward him rather than someone else. What you and IT suggested was that I take him out and draw with you two. I could not advance against you, so I had to get FRA to move from the South.

If I get a shot at a solo I might take it, who knows. However, we have one common goal - to reduce the number of survivors - I don't want a mass draw and unless you 'centralize' you won't make it.
3 AUSTRIA -> GERMANY: I will think on it... I also would rather avoid a mass draw, however my ability to keep you from a solo without Italy and now Russia is unfortunately limited (though in the last league, I did hold out for a 2 way draw with you when I could have taken a solo, so perhaps you will do likewise). Additionally, just as you do not want to betray France due to his help earlier, so I do not want to betray Italy (who has been a staunch ally).

Where would you invision the final borders being?
4 GERMANY -> AUSTRIA: The way things stand I have a good shot for a 2-way draw with FRA in the end. You have all deadlocked yourself and I can't see how anyone can actually make any move, in any direction.

I'm not really sure if there's much I can really offer at that stage, the simple fact is that we have a deadlock ourselves with RUS, where you are neither taking him out nor letting me take him out.

If you have a specific suggestion I'd be happy to hear it, but I see no reason to change course now. Bulk up or you'll die, this is my only advice at this stage.
